h1.p:
Common juniper (

 Juniperus communis

), a sprawling shrub, is widely distributed on rocky soils throughout the Northern Hemisphere. Many ornamental cultivars have been developed.

The savin (

 J. sabina

) of central Europe, Chinese juniper (

 J. chinensis

) of eastern Asia, and creeping juniper (

 J. horizontalis

) of eastern North America are other popular ornamental species with many horticultural varieties.

The wood of incense, or Spanish, juniper (

 J. thurifera

), of Spain and Portugal, and of Phoenician juniper (

 J. phoenicea

) of the Mediterranean region sometimes is burned as incense.
